    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Albert Einstein (1879-1955) was a German-born theoretical physicist, best known for his theory 
of relativity and specifically the equation for massâ€“energy equivalence, E = mc 2. Einstein received the 1921 
Nobel Prize in Physics.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Albert Einstein Collection</emph> comprises one item of outgoing correspondence and one original 
manuscript.  Written in his capacity as chair of the Emergency Committee of Atomic Scientists, the <emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph> (one letter) is an 
appeal for funding to educate the public about the uses of atomic energy.  The 11-page <emph render="bold">Manuscript</emph>, undated, is 
a research paper entitled "Uber rotationssymmetrishe stationare Gravitationsfelder" which includes text and 
numerous mathematical calculations.</p>
    </scopecontent>
